message.content:
A maraca is a percussive instrument typically made of a gourd or synthetic material.
It is often decorated with colorful patterns or designs.
The maraca usually has a cylindrical or oval shape with a small handle for holding and shaking.
The exterior of the maraca is smooth and may have a glossy or matte finish.
When shaken, it produces a distinctive rattling sound.
Maracas are commonly used in Latin American music, particularly in salsa and other genres with a strong beat.
They can be found in music stores, as well as in the hands of musicians and dancers around the world.
